<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gargoth McGreggor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-18 22:26:22</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hail Fellow Adventurers!<BR>
<BR>
    I have personally retrieved the shard from the portion of the question concerning Slaythe (The Froglok Assasin).  He is on average between levels 19-22 and is of a Monk Type Class.  (He uses some inate ability which encases you in fire.  Area effect also.)  As a level 23 warrior I was able to easily slay him and retrieve the leg to return to Bronin.  I am currently camping Faldor Hendrys in Qeynos and will fill you in on those details later.<BR>
<BR>
    Some of what the above information doesn't tell you is the following:<BR>
<BR>
Bronin is in the southernmost tower along the wall that seperates Misty.  You must have good faction with Deeppockets guild in order for him to cooperate.  If you wish to increase your faction with him without hurting your faction with anyone else...then purchase about 100-200 bandages and (as you are looking away from the zone to RV) follow the wall to the left.  In the corner is a small hut with a guy named Rangl Honeybugger (Or something like that) He claims he was attacked by a swarm of Bixies and needs bandages.  Give him 1 at a time to increase your faction with Deeppockets as well as the city merchants and guards.<BR>
<BR>
After you ask Bronin, "What Small Favor?"  He will tell you that a Froglok assasin has been hired to kill him.  The assasin spawns 20 seconds after you ask Bronin that question.  Simply get down from the tower and run through the gate to the other side of the wall and head for the northernmost corner of the wall.  Right next to the last big tree stump you will see Slaythe.  (I actually did this quest, but I also "Force Spawned" him to help me level hehe)<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helps....take care!<BR>
<BR>
-Gargoth McGreggor  (Tarrew Marr)</font></td></tr></table>
