<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Oakshot Stormfury</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-06 23:23:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay, quick notes for those that haven't done it yet.<BR>
<BR>
1. Beno is in the Dwarven Warrior's guild, in the door, up the stairs to the right. Stormguard faction has to be at least amiable. The Cleaner VII is not needed, just need amiable or better.<BR>
<BR>
2. Slaythe is about 20-22, I didn't fight him, a mage was camping him for the exp, he just let me loot the leg. You don't need good faction to turn in the leg, but he won't spawn if your faction isn't good enough to get Bronin to talk. See the notes before mine for great tips on Bronin and faction. (Gonna try those myself!)<BR>
<BR>
3. Faldor spawns in the back room of Crow's place, next to the secret door to the Rogue's Guild (Oops, wasn't supposed to tell!)  He was high blue to my 26 Druid, but has lousy magic resistance, so he went down surprisingly fast. Oh, don't let him get behind you, he backstabbed me for 85 as I was trying to pull him outta Crow's.  Took me 2 days to find him, he spawned early one morning.<BR>
<BR>
4. The guy looking for the Jailer and Banker, just hand the stuff to 'em.  Make sure you've got the right items, and hand them over.  See the quest description.<BR>
<BR>
5. The Axe is pretty cool, and acts as a lightsource, about equal to a regular lightstone.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck guys.</font></td></tr></table>
